Subject: [PATCH] Wrap AUDIO_GET_PTS use in #ifdef

The AUDIO_GET_PTS ioctl was removed from mainline Linux. saa716x_ff_main.c
still references it in a switch case for the legacy DVB audio device
interface. Out-of-tree builds against modern mainline fail with:

    error: 'AUDIO_GET_PTS' undeclared

Wrap the case statement in #ifdef AUDIO_GET_PTS so it compiles out on
kernels where the ioctl no longer exists. The switch falls through to
the default branch returning -ENOIOCTLCMD, which is the correct behavior
for an unsupported ioctl.

Affects 1 file: drivers/media/pci/saa716x/saa716x_ff_main.c.
---
diff --git a/drivers/media/pci/saa716x/saa716x_ff_main.c b/drivers/media/pci/saa716x/saa716x_ff_main.c
index a013aee..659e536 100644
--- a/drivers/media/pci/saa716x/saa716x_ff_main.c
+++ b/drivers/media/pci/saa716x/saa716x_ff_main.c
@@ -427,11 +427,13 @@ static int do_dvb_audio_ioctl(struct dvb_device *dvbdev,
 	int ret = 0;
 
 	switch (cmd) {
+#ifdef AUDIO_GET_PTS
 	case AUDIO_GET_PTS:
 	{
 		*(u64 *)parg = sti7109->audio_pts;
 		break;
 	}
+#endif
 	default:
 		ret = -ENOIOCTLCMD;
 		break;
